/em\u003e. You’ll need it for some crucial upgrades that will allow you to take on some of the most powerful \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/monster-hunter-wilds-guide/526019/monster-list-roster-all-unlock-order\"\u003emonsters\u003c/a\u003e in the game.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn this \u003cem\u003eMonster Hunter Wilds\u003c/em\u003e guide, we’ll walk you through \u003cstrong\u003ehow to get Fucium Ore\u003c/strong\u003e and what kinds of items you might want to use it on.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp id=\"where-to-mine-fucium-ore-in-monster-hunter-wilds\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003eWhere to mine Fucium Ore in Monster Hunter Wilds\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"1080\" data-pswp-width=\"1920\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A Hunter hover over a Mining Outcrop in Monster Hunter Wilds\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=376 376w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=384 384w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=415 415w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=480 480w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=540 540w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=640 640w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=750 750w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=828 828w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1080 1080w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1200 1200w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h49m22s726.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eImage: Capcom via Polygon\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eOnce you unlock the High Rank version of the\u003cstrong\u003e Ruins of Wyveria\u003c/strong\u003e — which you can do by progressing the post-credits \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/monster-hunter-wilds-guide/525454/walkthrough-main-story-quest-steps-list-all-hunts\"\u003equestline\u003c/a\u003e in \u003cem\u003eMonster Hunter Wilds\u003c/em\u003e — you’ll be able to farm as much Fucium Ore as you want.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eLoad into the Ruins of Wyveria and set a marker on one of the \u003cstrong\u003eMining Outcrops\u003c/strong\u003e — there’s one just out of the base camp and to the left. Your mount should automatically take you to the ore.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eMine the rock and you’ll have a chance to get Fucium Ore. While it’s pretty common, it’s still considered a “rare” ore, so not every Mining Outcrop is guaranteed to have it. Ride your mount from Mining Outcrop to Mining Outcrop until you eventually find some.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"1080\" data-pswp-width=\"1920\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A Hunter mines Fucium Ore in Monster Hunter Wilds\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=376 376w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=384 384w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=415 415w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=480 480w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=540 540w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=640 640w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=750 750w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=828 828w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1080 1080w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1200 1200w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h34m11s543.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eImage: Capcom via Polygon\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eIf you exhaust all the Mining Outcrops in the Ruins of Wyveria and still need more Fucium Ore, wait for the Mining Outcrops to respawn, load into a new area and come back, or just restart your game. If you’re looking for a specific amount of Fucium to build an upgrade (more on that below), try \u003cstrong\u003ewishlisting \u003c/strong\u003ethe item so the game will tell you when you’ve gathered enough.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp id=\"what-to-use-fucium-ore-for-in-monster-hunter-wilds\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003eWhat to use Fucium Ore for in Monster Hunter Wilds\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"1080\" data-pswp-width=\"1920\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A Hunter builds a powerful Metal Bagpipe using Fucium Ore in Monster Hunter Wilds\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=376 376w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=384 384w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=415 415w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=480 480w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=540 540w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=640 640w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=750 750w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=828 828w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1080 1080w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1200 1200w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/vlcsnap-2025-03-03-14h33m26s107.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eImage: Capcom via Polygon\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eFucium Ore is mostly used for \u003cstrong\u003eupgrading non-monster weapons and crafting non-monster armor pieces\u003c/strong\u003e. Some pieces in the decently powerful Ingot armor set, for example, require Fucium Ore.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSimilarly, you might need Fucium Ore to upgrade the metal or hope versions of certain weapons. Even if you never intend to use these weapons, you may want to build other weapons off of them. Because weapons in \u003cem\u003eMonster Hunter Wilds\u003c/em\u003e upgrade based on a tree, you need the previous versions of weapons to upgrade them to their final forms. For example, you need to use Fucium Ore to craft the Metal Bagpipe 3 if you want to eventually craft the Jin Dhaang 1 Hunting Horn. Other weapons have similar upgrade pipelines that require Fucium Ore.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eNeed help navigating the Forbidden Lands? Our \u003cem\u003eMonster Hunter Wilds\u003c/em\u003e guides can outline your progress with our \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/525454\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003emain story walkthrough\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/526019\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003emonster list\u003c/a\u003e ahead of reaching \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/528902\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003eHigh Rank\u003c/a\u003e, help you settle on an armament with our \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/529947\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003eweapons list\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/528911\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003ebest weapons\u003c/a\u003e explainers, and teach you how to uncover \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/528887\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003eores\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/528892\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003ebones\u003c/a\u003e, and get \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/528353\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003emonster tails\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
